metadata.name: ASSEMBLING MACHINE #61
metadata.description:
The machine never sleeps.
Build. Construct. Develop. Create. Form. Produce. Generate. Repeat.
---------------
Collectors at the highest tier (125 tez) may claim a signed 8”x10” print of their mint. Please look for details about prints on Twitter (@teaboswell), or contact me directly
---------------
CONTROLS:
A - Toggle loading animation (off by default to improve performance)
S - Download image
Double tap (mobile) - Download image
1-6 - Modify scale (1 = default, 2048 x 2730px, 6 = maximum, 12288 x 16380px (very performance intensive, will take a long time to render))
F - Fit to current screen size
G - Toggle grain overlay
L - Toggle background grid lines
B - Cycle border sizes (0 -> 100 -> 200 -> 300px)

You can modify the x and y url parameters to set a custom size. Note that the image will change to fit the new size, but overall drawing style, colors, etc. will remain the same.
(For example, for a 1000x2000 image, add &x=1000&y=2000)

metadata.name: Beautiful M1nds #12
metadata.description:
This project is dedicated to the beautiful minds of the last centuries. I am talking about philosophy, math, science, physics, everything related to human knowledge.

I chosen 6 illustrious thinkers: Karl Marx, Stephen Hawking, Albert Einstein, Nikola Tesla, Sigmund Freud and Alan Turing. Each one of them made the world to step forward on different perspectives.

The algorithm is creating the famous iconic shapes of the beautiful minds using only letters, and the letters are just taken from their own books:
Karl Marx - Das Kapital
Sigmund Freud - The Interpretation of Dreams
Stephen Hawking - Particle Creation by Black Holes
Nikola Tesla - The Inventions Researches and Writings
Albert Einstein - Relativity
Alan Turing - Computing Machinery and Intelligence

There are 3 features:
The Font
The Size of the Font
The Author

The smaller is the font size, the more accurate becomes the image.
This is a tribute to human knowledge but also to Visual Poetry Art or Data Poetry and phenomenal artists like Jiri Kolar.

metadata.name: Deep Space Grid - AI Study III #71
metadata.description:
Deep Space Grid uses experimentation with lines, shapes, color and opacity through the exploration of faux space charts.

Adjusts to monitor size, best viewed in fullscreen mode.

This project is a generative art experiment using a Text2Code workflow. The JavaScript code for this project was written entirely by AI using GPT-3. None of the code was altered or created by a human aside from changing Math.random() with fxrand().

Text2Code study #3 /// Project CoDexter by @BrainArtLabs

metadata.name: Block Dock #47
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

Is it a space dock? Is it a ship dock? Where are they docking... and why?

'Block Dock' is a playful exploration of scale, form and color.

In live mode:
Click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 1500x1500px PNG.
